  "_about": "Maps FinMg granular budget categories onto the NSWTG super-lines used by both the Annual Accounts (Section C, actuals) and the Plan (Section D, forecasts). Direction selects deposit vs withdrawal. Categories NOT listed under any line are intentionally unmapped: the NSWTG forms have no clean home for day-to-day personal-living spend (groceries, medicine, personal cashout, fast food, fashion, nicotine, home, office, misc). The audit/gap engine surfaces the unallocated total so Linda allocates it deliberately rather than the system guessing. Tunable: edit categories here, no code change.",
